<br>
I understand the point you are trying to make. I really think alot of it has to do with how Verant has set up the high level end of the game. The goals are alot different now then they were back in the &quot;good ole days&quot;.<br>
<br>
Things basically have to be more guild focused now. The time and energy involved entails alot more then it used to. So when guilds set out to achieve thier goals they become much more focused on thier guild benefitting from that work and energy spent. The idea is to benefit the guild so that they are more able to accomplish thier future goals. This usually means not inviting non-guilded people along, so that someone in the guild who is going to be there for the next step in goals, will have a better chance at drops which end up benefitting the guild. Who knows when you might see the non-guilded person again.<br>
<br>
I know this seems very self-centered and selfish. I wish it wasn't this way. But really Verant set up the camps and the quests and the high end game to be this way. To accomplish certain goals you can't just let every Tom, Dick and Hairy along to benefit from your hard work or you will never end up accomplishing the goals. So people have taken on the attitude of &quot;If you aren't in my guild then get lost&quot;.<br>
<br>
When it comes to the smaller things like SoWs, Ports, Rezzes.. Thats more of an individual decision and not based on any tag. People asking for these things are alot more rude about it then it used to be. I get tells when I am in HoT from people asking me to C3 them when they are in Sebilis, and get rude replies when I explain I am a bit busy. I know clerics go through the samething with rezzes, wizards and druids with ports and so on. <p>Crackanna Breeze<BR>
Leader of Gray Soldiers<BR>
Controller of the simplest minds.<BR>
