I do find it inconvenient when I'm not selling a service, to receive a tell requesting it.  The demand for xlocates, ports, crack, and rezzes are high.  Why? Because the people that want them don't want to waste their time getting from point a to point b, or filling those bubbles back up.  To fault someone who wasn't actively selling one of the above for being rude makes me think the person taking offense might want to self reflect a little, and be sensitive to the time being vested in them by the providing player.   If you don't like the terms you can always choose to interrupt someone else's gameplay with a tell.<br>
<br>
